<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>Vin's Blog (Proxy)</title><link>http://carlosvin.github.io/</link><description></description><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Sun, 15 Jun 2014 22:15:19 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>http://getnikola.com/</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>Git proxy configuration</title><link>http://carlosvin.github.io/en/posts/git-proxy-config.html</link><dc:creator>Carlos Martín Sánchez</dc:creator><description>&lt;p&gt;Sometimes working through a proxy is pretty tedious.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are going how to configure git to work through a proxy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A generic description, how to make git uses a specific proxy:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code bash literal-block"&gt;
&lt;span class="c"&gt;#http
&lt;/span&gt;git config --global http.proxy &amp;lt;protocol&amp;gt;://&amp;lt;user_name&amp;gt;:&amp;lt;password&amp;gt;@&amp;lt;ip_host&amp;gt;:&amp;lt;port&amp;gt;

&lt;span class="c"&gt;#https
&lt;/span&gt;git config --global https.proxy &amp;lt;protocol&amp;gt;://&amp;lt;user_name&amp;gt;:&amp;lt;password&amp;gt;@&amp;lt;ip_host&amp;gt;:&amp;lt;port&amp;gt;

&lt;span class="c"&gt;#to disable using proxy
&lt;/span&gt;git config --global --unset http.proxy
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;More info in &lt;a class="reference external" href="http://git-scm.com/docs/git-config"&gt;official Git configuration&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
